Class InkRecognizerAsyncClient

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.microsoft.azure.cognitiveservices.inkrecognizer.InkRecognizerAsyncClient

  • public final class InkRecognizerAsyncClient
extends Object
    The InkRecognizerAsyncClient communicates with the service using default configuration settings or settings provided by the caller. Service results are returned asynchronously.

      • recognizeInk

        public reactor.core.publisher.Mono<Response<InkRecognitionRoot>> recognizeInk(Iterable<InkStroke> strokes,
                                                                              String language)
        Synchronously sends data to the service and generates a tree structure containing the recognition results.
        Parameters:
        strokes - The ink strokes to recognize.
        language - The IETF BCP 47 language code (for ex. en-US, en-GB, hi-IN etc.) for the strokes. This is only needed when the language is different from the default set when the client was instantiated.
        Returns:
        An InkRecognitionResult containing status codes, error messages (if applicable) and the recognition results in a hierarchy.

      • recognizeInk

        public reactor.core.publisher.Mono<Response<InkRecognitionRoot>> recognizeInk(Iterable<InkStroke> strokes,
                                                                              InkPointUnit unit,
                                                                              float multiple,
                                                                              ApplicationKind applicationKind,
                                                                              String language)
        Synchronously sends data to the service and generates a tree structure containing the recognition results.
        Parameters:
        strokes - The ink strokes to recognize.
        unit - The physical unit for the points in the stroke.
        multiple - A multiplier applied to the unit value to indicate the true unit being used. This allows the caller to specify values in a fraction or multiple of a unit.
        applicationKind - The domain of the application (Writing or Drawing. The default is "Mixed").
        language - The IETF BCP 47 language code (for ex. en-US, en-GB, hi-IN etc.) for the strokes. This is only needed when the language is different from the default set when the client was instantiated.
        Returns:
        A InkRecognitionResult containing status codes, error messages (if applicable) and the recognition results in a hierarchy.
